.TH "clk_bulk_disable" 9 "clk_bulk_disable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
clk_bulk_disable \- gate a set of clocks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" clk_bulk_disable
.BI "(int num_clks "  ","
.BI "const struct clk_bulk_data *clks "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "num_clks" 12
the number of clk_bulk_data
.IP "clks" 12
the clk_bulk_data table being gated
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
clk_bulk_disable must not sleep, which differentiates it from
clk_bulk_unprepare. clk_bulk_disable must be called before
clk_bulk_unprepare.
